    <div style="min-height:500px; font-size:large">
    Silicon Institue of Technology is an engineering institution situated in Bhubaneswar, Odisha.
    The college was established in 2001 as an affiliated college of the Utkal University and the college has been an affiliated college of Biju Patnaik University of Technology(BPUT).
    The college is accredited by the National Board of Accreditation and was granted autonomy by University Grants Commission(UGC) in 2017 for a period of 10 years.
        <br />
    In 2009,Silicon Institute of Technology,Sambalpur was established as its sister institution.
    The institution is located in Silicon Hills,Patia in Bhubaneswar and at Silicon West,Sason,Sambalpur.SIT Bhubaneswar campus is spread over 14146 Acres.
        <br />
    Students re admitted to the college through the Joint Entrance Examination(main) merit list of Government of India.
        <br />
    SIT Bhubaneswar offers 9 courses across 2 streams namely Engineering,IT and across 3 degrees like B.Tech,M.Tech and MCA.
        <br />
    Hostel facility is available for its students.
    Additional campus facilities such as Electronics lab,Computer Lab,Academic zone,A/C,Play ground,Canteen,Cafeteria,E-library,club facilities are also there.
        <br />
    Both locations have campuses with activities of more than two thousand students,about two thousand alumni and four hundred and fifty staff members.
        <br />
    The National Institutional Ranking Framework(NIRF) ranked it 179 among engineering colleges in 2020.
    SiliconTech's Innovative Council is ranked as Best Institution Innovative Council(IIC),East Zone.
        <br />
    SiliconTech was awarded the Best Technincal Institute Award in Research and Development in the Odisha Technological Conclave 2019.
    SiliconTech is categorized as 'Band B' institution(rank between 26-50)in category of 'Private or Self-Finanaced Colleges/Institutes in Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements(ARIIA)2020. 


